Six students have been suspended from Alliance High School following cases of bullying, the board of management has said.Acting board chairman Sam Ncheeri in a statement on Saturday admitted that there have been cases of bullying at the school. He said 10 prefects, including the School Captain, have been demoted.&ldquo;The school board wishes to express our concern and address particulars relating to the matter,&rdquo; he said. Ncheeri said there is an ongoing investigation against the deputy principal.Ncheeri said there have been serious cases of indiscipline, including bullying, and the board would like to apologise to the students and the parents.He assured students and parents of safety, saying adequate measures have been taken to ensure bullying never happens again.